The Handball Federation of Nigeria (HFN) have said the Prudent Energy Premier League and every other programme in the country have been postponed indefinitely due to the spread of coronavirus in the country. The Secretary General of HFN Maigidasanma Mohammed who released a statement to that effect, said that the decision to suspend all handball activities was borne out of a directive from the Federal Ministry of Youths and Sports instructing all sports federation to stop all competitions. “The Handball Federation of Nigeria is in receipt of a letter from the Ministry of youths and sports stopping federations from all national and international championships. “In view of the above our earlier scheduled Prudent Energy Handball Premier League is hereby postponed indefinitely until the issues around COVID-19 becomes clear”. The HFN also urged the handball family to remain safe and observe social distancing so as to prevent the spread of the virus.  